<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING COMPRESSOR AND CLUTCH, TWO CYLINDER RECIPROCATING TYPE - After 01/01/1993 (R-134a) -
        TROUBLESHOOTING
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="check" graphiccount="0">
        <title>TROUBLESHOOTING</title>
        <table id="t1601701" tblwidth="full-page">
            <title>Troubleshooting Chart</title>
            <tgroup cols="3">
                <colspec colnum="1" colname="1" colwidth="1.5in"/>
                <colspec colnum="2" colname="2" colwidth="2.25in"/>
                <colspec colnum="3" colname="3" colwidth="3.25in" colsep="1"/>
                <thead valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Condition</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Cause</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Remedy</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry morerows="8">
                            <para>Compressor Noisy and/or Vibrating</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>A/C system overcharged</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Discharge and re-charge system. Refer to GROUP 16 - AIR CONDITIONING BASIC THEORY,
                                SYSTEM DIAGNOSIS AND SERVICE.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Incorrect amount of oil in system</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Check oil level in compressor. Refer to
                                <hotlnk document="s16017x_HL1601706.xml" xrefid="hl1601706">LUBRICATION</hotlnk>.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Belts loose.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Tighten to correct specifications. Refer to
                                <hotlnk document="s16017x_13.xml" xrefid="hl1601702">SPECIFICATIONS</hotlnk>.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Clutch pulley misaligned.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Adjust compressor mounting to align drive pulleys.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Pulley assembly loose on shaft.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Remove the pulley assembly and check the shaft taper and key. If the taper inside the
                                pulley assembly is damaged, replace the pulley assembly. If the compressor shaft taper
                                is damaged, replace the compressor.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Clutch bearing is bad.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Replace pulley assembly.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Foreign material or damaged parts in the compressor</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Replace compressor.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Compressor crankcase bearings worn or damaged.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Replace compressor.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Compressor mounting is loose or broken.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Repair and/or tighten mounting brackets.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry morerows="3">
                            <para>Clutch Inoperative</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Check belts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace and/or tighten. Refer to Belt Tension
                                <hotlnk document="s16017x_13.xml" xrefid="hl1601702">Specifications</hotlnk>.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Check the field coil leads and connector.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Repair or replace as required.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Check for voltage at coil when A/C is engaged.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Repair as required to get clutch to engage. Refer to GROUP 08 - ELECTRICAL
                                TROUBLESHOOTING MANUAL in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual for the vehicle being
                                serviced.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Check thermostat control switch for operation.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Refer to GROUP 08 - ELECTRICAL TROUBLESHOOTING MANUAL for the vehicle being serviced.
                                Replace if not operating or out of adjustment.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry>
                            <para>High Suction Pressure, Low Discharge Pressure</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Check head gaskets and valve plate.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>If gaskets are leaking or valve plate is damaged or worn, replace with a head, valve
                                plate kit.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
